    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - AIR SYSTEM - ROADRANGER VALVE A-5010</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ROADRANGER VALVE A-5010</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302908">Figure 8</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal and Disassembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two screws holding the bottom cover to the valve and slide the cover down the
                    gear shift lever to expose the air line fittings. Disconnect air lines.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the jam nut and turn the control valve from the gear shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pry the medallion from the recess in the top cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two screws to separate the top cover from the valve housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two screws on the side of the valve housing to separate the housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Range Preselection Lever from the left housing and the position balls and
                    guide from the lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, remove the spring and O-ring from the bores in the left housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, remove the springs, O-ring and sleeve from the bores in the right
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Reassembly and Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302908">Figure 8</hotlnk>
                    for proper reassembly. Use a VERY SMALL amount of silicone lubricant on the O-rings to avoid
                    clogging the ports. A small amount of grease on the position springs and balls will help to hold
                    them in place during reassembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302908" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302908" filename="../figg13/G1302908.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Roadranger Valve A-5010</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the control valve on the gear shift lever and tighten the jam nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the air lines and install the bottom cover.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
